claim.claim-text:
7. A method of producing the compound of claim 1 comprising the sequential steps of:
 a) reacting phosphorus oxychloride with a C12-18 fatty alcohol;
 b) reacting the resultant compound of step “a” with a hydroxybenzaldehyde, thereby forming a phosphodiester compound;
 c) reacting said phosphodiester compound with a cyanoethanol to form a phosphotriester compound;
 d) reacting said phosphotriester compound with Deoxofluor, wherein said reaction with Deoxofluor is optionally preceded by reducing said phosphotriester compound with sodium borohydride, thereby producing a fluorinated compound; and
 e) deprotecting the resultant fluorinated compound of step “d”.
